name: Home in Amsterdam · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood is one of the most beautiful in Amsterdam! You overlook the Amstel river, the Skinny Bridge, Carré theater and the Hermitage museum. It is a fairly quiet neighborhood with the hustle and bustle within easy reach. For example, you can go shopping in the Utrechtsestraat just around the corner, it is a two-minute walk to the Rembrandtplein, the Kalverstraat (the biggest shopping area) is also a 5-minute walk.

Built during the city's Golden Age, the three parallel canals are connected by streets lined with shops, food and drink. The Grachtengordel consists of the Herengracht, Keizersgracht and Prinsengracht, closed by the Amstel river. In a sense, the Grachtengordel is a crossing from the more bustling Center to the softer suburbs of Jordaan, Museumwijk and De Pijp. The Canal Ring encompasses the city's two main entertainment and culture squares. On Leidseplein you will find legendary concert halls such as Paradiso and Melkweg. Rembrandtplein has several bars,

name: Rental unit in Amsterdam · ★4.76 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Built during the city’s Golden Age, the three parallel canals are interconnected with streets filled with shopping, eating and drinking opportunities. The Canal Ring is made up of Herengracht, Keizersgracht and Prinsengracht. In a way, the Canal Ring forms a crossover from the more bustling Centre to the gentler outer neighbourhoods of Jordaan, Museum District and De Pijp. The Canal Ring includes the city’s two main nightlife and culture squares. Leidseplein features such legendary concert halls as Paradiso and Melkweg. Rembrandtplein has several bars, two large nightclubs (Escape and Air), and ‘old world’ evocative treasures such as De Kroon and Café Schiller. The whole area is dotted with Amsterdam's beloved neighbourhood ‘brown cafes'.

name: Bed and breakfast in Amsterdam · ★4.44 · 1 bedroom · 3 beds · 1 private bath
host_about:
Hotel Not Hotel Amsterdam is a place where a room isn’t just a room, but a work of art with its own creator, story, and identity. Most of them designed and specially made by Collaboration-O, a group of young designers that originated from the Eindhoven Design Academy, and one by Arno Coenen and his partner IRIS.

When you wake up, you step into an art-filled, exhibition-like space instead of an anonymous lobby or hallway. The entire hotel is one big living room, with cosy seating areas between the cottages. Combined with our luxury beds and other facilities, Hotel Not Hotel offers an unrivalled experience. 
Besides all this, we feel that the value of a city lies in experiencing its local day-to-day life. As we are closely connected to Amsterdam and its numerous creative entrepreneurs, we know where to send you for a night on the town, a hidden culinary gem, or an upcoming artist’s exhibition. 

The bar connected to Hotel Not Hotel is called Kevin Bacon. Just like the actor, the bar has zero pretention, it always delivers, and it makes sure everybody has a good time.

Kevin Bacon is not your typical hotel bar. It’s where locals get their morning coffee or a quick breakfast. It’s where friends meet for a cocktail or a beer before diving into the nightlife, and where hotel guests let their hair down after a long day in the city.

When the weather is good, the ‘Whitey the White’ terrace is sunny like a perfectly fried egg. The staff’s friendly attitude shines all year round.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan area and canals are nothing but highlights. Throughout the world-famous canals maze-like streets offer hidden courtyards. Originally a working-class neighbourhood, this district has become one of the most expensive, upscale locations in the Netherlands. It is home too many art galleries and is also dotted with speciality shops and restaurants. Tons of nice restaurants and clubs (Salmuera, Lion Noir, Palladium, Jimmy Woo, Chicago Social Club, Chin Chin Club).

Within a three-min walking distance from he Anne Frank house, the Wester Church, the Dam Square and the famous Noordermarkt (biological food market each Saturday and textile market each Monday).

Around ten-min walking distance you will find the Museum Square, the Van Gogh Museum and the Vondelpark.

Enjoy the little design boutiques with furniture, clothes and jewellery on the well known ''9 straatjes'' (9 streets).

name: Rental unit in Amsterdam · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Onze charmante straat, gelegen midden in het bruisende hart van Amsterdam, biedt een unieke en vredige ontsnapping in de stad. Het voelt bijna dorpsachtig aan, met een rustige sfeer die een welkome afwisseling biedt van de drukte van de stad.

Op slechts een steenworp afstand bevindt zich de levendige Utrechtsestraat, een ware schat vol met gezellige kroegjes, cafes, boetiekjes en bruisende winkels. Hier kun je heerlijk rondslenteren, de lokale cultuur proeven en genieten van de warme gastvrijheid van Amsterdam.

Bovendien ben je binnen enkele minuten bij het water en de prachtige grachten van Amsterdam, waar je kunt genieten van schilderachtige uitzichten en ontspannende wandelingen langs de waterkant. En als je de stad verder wilt verkennen, liggen iconische buurten zoals de Pijp en het Rembrandtplein op minder dan tien minuten loopafstand. Hier ontmoet de rust van onze straat het bruisende leven van de stad, waardoor je de perfecte balans hebt voor een onvergetel

name: Rental unit in Amsterdam · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp (Dutch pronunciation: [də ˈpɛip]; English: The Pipe) is a neighbourhood of Amsterdam, Netherlands. It is located directly south of Amsterdam's city centre and it is part of the borough Amsterdam-Zuid, in a part of the city known as the Old South (Oud Zuid). It is served by De Pijp metro station. Most streets in De Pijp are named after Dutch painters, like Jan Steen, Frans Hals, Ruysdael and Vincent van Gogh. Diamantbuurt, Nieuwe Pijp and Oude Pijp are the three districts composing the area.

The busiest street market of the Netherlands, the Albert Cuyp Market, is located in De Pijp. It is open six days per week and attracts tourists. The former Heineken brewery is also a local tourist attraction; the former town hall of Nieuwer-Amstel is one of De Pijp's most notable monuments. Next to the former Heineken brewery is the Marie Heinekenplein, which has a number of bars and cafes. Along the canal Ruysdaelkade, there is a small red-light district.

neighborhood_overview:
Living by the canal - that is a dream for many. In the past, however, this was considered frowned upon and not classical enough. Therefore the canal was filled up around 16th century. A beautiful park in the middle of the city was created - and still is today. Large trees that provide shade in summer and absorb the sounds of the city.
I love the Cafe Slijterij Oosterling (50m from us). Open since 1877, this is probably one of the most authentic places in Amsterdam. Time seems to stand still here. If you are hungry, you can get delicious sandwiches, burgers, salads or freshly caught fish in the Brasserie Nel (400m). If you prefer self-catering and our shared kitchen, the supermarket is only 70m away.

name: Hostel in Amsterdam · ★4.67 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Cocomama has quite an interesting history. Believe it or not, but before we turned it into the city's first (and only) boutique hostel, it used to be a well-known brothel. We kept the marble entrance, royal round staircase, original chandeliers and high ceilings in place – the rest we let go of (sorry guys).

We're only one block away from the Albert Cuyp market, Europe's largest daily open-air market. We (and our wallets) love the stalls – offering anything from fresh produce, Dutch street-food, to the latest in fashion (well girls, not sure about the last one, but it's definitely fun to have a look around).

Tram-stop, supermarket, museums, cafés, restaurants, canals, park – anything one needs when visiting Amsterdam is on a stone's throw away. It's as central and easy as it gets.

neighborhood_overview:
The Staatsliedenbuurt is a vibrant residential neighborhood located in the west-central part of Amsterdam, just a short distance from the city center. It is a popular area for young professionals and families alike, with a diverse mix of residents from all walks of life.

The neighborhood is known for its charming, tree-lined streets and beautiful architecture, with many of the buildings dating back to the early 20th century. There are also plenty of green spaces in the area, including the Westerpark, which is a popular spot for jogging, picnicking, and attending cultural events.

In terms of amenities, the Staatsliedenbuurt has a lot to offer. There are plenty of restaurants, cafes, and bars to choose from, as well as a variety of shops and supermarkets. The neighborhood is also well-connected to public transportation, making it easy to reach other parts of the city.

Zoku is very conveniently located in the Eastern Canal District, in the heart of Amsterdam. On arterial "Weesperstraat", the building is easily accessible by car, bicycle and public transport (only a 3 minute walk to metros, busses and trams!). Being 10 minutes away from the Central Station by metro and 15 minutes from the city's business districts, the "RAI" and the "Zuidas" (South Axis), it's truly a hub from which any important location in the city can be easily reached. Zoku is also within cuddling distance of the city's main cultural, entertainment and shopping areas.
Wish to explore the city the Amsterdam way? We have bikes for rent that will give you the freedom to roam wherever you want, whilst blending in with the locals. Our Sidekicks know all there is to know about the city's hidden gems and local places-to-be. Just give them a little nudge, they love to pass on local knowledge!
host_about: Zoku is a re-invented apartment hotel brand facilitating global living and working. A place you can call a second home, even on your first visit. Zoku creates a new category in the hotel industry: a hybrid between a home and an office with the services of a hotel topped with the social buzz of a thriving neighborhood. Zoku is suitable for people who live and work in a city for a period of between five days and three months. Zoku offers the travelling professional a global nomad’s home base through a smart loft (private areas) and social spaces (communal areas) to work, sleep, play and live in. Zoku gives the mobile professional time and space to customize their own living- and working area, meet peers, enhance their business network, live an asset-light lifestyle and generally have a good time.

Nieuwendammerdijk, the historic 'most beautiful street in Amsterdam Noord', with houses which predate the oldest in the city center, is 10 mins walk away through the park.

Cycle 15 minutes and you can reach the beautiful Dutch villages of Durgerdam or Ransdorp.

There's a great, new, architecture-prize-winning swimming pool, the Noorderparkbad, 10 mins cycle away.

Experience Amsterdam like a local from our amazing location! Our place is just steps away from everything Amsterdam has to offer, with the world-famous Rijksmuseum right across the street. Immerse yourself in the city's rich cultural scene with the Museumquarter on our doorstep, including the van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, and Moco Museum.

With a plethora of amazing restaurants in the area, you won't have to venture far to satisfy your cravings. Explore the famous Amsterdam canals or stroll down the multiple shopping streets just minutes away. And don't forget to visit the trendy neighborhood of "the Pijp," with its vibrant local restaurants, bars, and shops.

Take a canal cruise right across the street, or enjoy a relaxing walk through the beautiful Vondelpark, both within easy walking distance. The Heineken Museum and the lively Albert Cuyp market are also just a stone's throw away.

name: Townhouse in Amsterdam · ★4.33 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Het huis staat in de buurt Tuindorp-Buiksloot. Dat is een wijk met arbeiderswoningen uit de jaren 1930 in Amsterdam-Noord. Noors is een opkomende buurt met veel ruimte voor leuke, vernieuwende horeca. De wijk ligt tussen een mooi stadspark; het Noorderpark, en een klein bos; het Vliegenbos. De verbinding tussen het centrum en noord gaat via een veerpont, die is op 10 minuten fietsafstand van ons huis. Met de metro, 5 minuten lopen, ben je in no time in het centrum. Als je de andere kant op fietst ben je zo in Waterland, een prachtig beschermd natuurgebied.

The Weesperzijde, is a beautiful street on the canal. Though nearby the citycentre, you have here a real Amsterdam feeling wih the boats passing by the house, beautiful view and walkingpaths leading to the centre. You will find many restaurants and bars around the corner, but our appartment you will experience as a nice quiet place in the middle of all of this. In summertime the waterside in front of our house is full with sunseekers, swimmers, little boats and terrasses.
You can also rent an electric boat nearby for exploring the canals.
But you can also enjoy the city from our rooftop.
